+<script>
+function revealNext() {
+    // Find the next hidden cloze and reveal it
+    var clozes = document.querySelectorAll('.cloze, .cloze-fallback');
+    for (var i = 0; i < clozes.length; i++) {
+        if (clozes[i].style.visibility === 'hidden') {
+            clozes[i].style.visibility = 'visible';
+            break;
+        }
+    }
+}
+
+function revealAll() {
+    // Reveal all clozes at once
+    var clozes = document.querySelectorAll('.cloze, .cloze-fallback');
+    for (var i = 0; i < clozes.length; i++) {
+        clozes[i].style.visibility = 'visible';
+    }
+}
+</script>
+
+<!-- Back -->
+{{Back}}
+```
+
+### Note Content
+
+```
+Text:
+This is a test [c1]card with [c2]multiple [c3]cloze [c4]deletions
+```
+
+### Setup
+
+1. Open Settings > Controls > User Actions
+2. Tap **User Action 1**
+3. Enter: `revealNext();`
+4. Save
+5. Still in User Action 1, tap to **Add Key**
+6. Press **H** (or any key you prefer)
+7. Save
+
+### Usage
+
+1. Open a cloze card for review
+2. Initially, all clozes are hidden
+3. Press **H**
+4. The first cloze becomes visible: `This is a test ____card with [c2]multiple...`
+5. Press **H** again
+6. Next cloze revealed: `This is a test ____card with multiple [c3]cloze...`
+7. Continue until all clozes are revealed
+
+## Available Files
+
+### Implementation Files
+
+1. **UserActionPreference.kt** (New)
+   - Custom EditTextPreference for entering user action JavaScript
+   - Displays configured code or "No JavaScript configured"
+
+2. **ViewerCommand.kt** (Modified)
+   - Adds USER_ACTION_1 through USER_ACTION_9 enum entries
+
+3. **card.js** (Modified)
+   - Adds JavaScript functions: userAction1() through userAction9()
+   - triggerUserAction() helper function
+
+4. **Reviewer.kt** (Modified)
+   - executeCommand() cases for user actions
+   - executeUserAction() helper method to execute JavaScript
+
+5. **AbstractFlashcardViewer.kt** (Modified)
+   - Signal constants for user actions
+   - Signal handling and processing
+
+6. **preferences_controls.xml** (Modified)
+   - User Action preferences now use UserActionPreference instead of ControlPreference
+
+### Documentation Files
+
+1. **IMPLEMENTATION_GUIDE.md** - Detailed implementation guide for developers
+2. **COMPLETE_IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md** - Complete summary of the implementation
+3. **TESTING_GUIDE.md** - Comprehensive testing guide with test cases
+4. **README.md** (this file) - Quick start guide
+
+## Technical Details
+
+### Architecture
+
+```
+User Input
+    ↓
+PeripheralKeymap / GestureProcessor
+    ↓
+ViewerCommand.USER_ACTION_1
+    ↓
+Reviewer.executeCommand()
+    ↓
+Reviewer.executeUserAction(1)
+    ↓
+Get JavaScript from preferences
+    ↓
+webView.evaluateJavascript()
+    ↓
+JavaScript executes in WebView
+    ↓
+Card DOM modified / Effects applied
+```
+
+### Preference Keys
+
+- `userAction1` through `userAction9` - Store JavaScript code
+- `binding_USER_ACTION_1` through `binding_USER_ACTION_9` - Key/gesture bindings
+
+### Signal Constants
+
+- `signal:user_action_1` through `signal:user_action_9`
+- Mapped to ViewerCommand enums
+
+## Use Cases
+
+### 1. Cloze Deletion Step-by-Step Reveal
+
+The most common use case - reveal clozes one at a time instead of all at once.
+
+### 2. Custom Keyboard Shortcuts
+
+Bind frequently used operations to keys:
+- Toggle hints
+- Show card info
+- Mark cards
+- Play audio
+
+### 3. Gamepad Integration
+
+Use game controllers for reviewing, with gamepad buttons triggering custom actions.
+
+### 4. Advanced Card Interactions
+
+Complex interactions:
+- Show/hide specific elements
+- Modify card appearance
+- Interactive card content
+- Dynamic content generation
+
+## Advanced Examples
+
+### Changing Card Appearance
+
+```javascript
+function toggleNightMode() {
+    var body = document.body;
+    if (body.style.backgroundColor === 'black') {
+        body.style.backgroundColor = 'white';
+        body.style.color = 'black';
+    } else {
+        body.style.backgroundColor = 'black';
+        body.style.color = 'white';
+    }
+}
+```
+
+### Displaying Debug Information
+
+```javascript
+function showDebug() {
+    console.log('Card type:', document.querySelector('.card').className);
+    console.log('Visible elements:', document.querySelectorAll(':visible').length);
+    alert('Debug info logged to console');
+}
+```
+
+### Custom Answer Handling
+
+```javascript
+function customAnswer() {
+    // Add a specific answer note
+    console.log('Answered with custom logic');
+    // Your custom logic here
+}
+```
+
+## Limitations
+
+1. **9 User Actions** - Limited to 9 configurable user actions
+2. **JavaScript Scope** - Functions must be globally accessible in card scope
+3. **Execution Context** - Code runs in WebView security context (same as card rendering)
+4. **No Synchronous Feedback** - JavaScript execution is asynchronous
+
+## Security
+
+- JavaScript runs in WebView sandbox
+- Only accesses card DOM
+- No network access beyond existing capabilities
+- User controls all code execution
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+### User Action Doesn't Work
+
+1. Check JavaScript code is valid
+2. Verify key/gesture binding is set
+3. Check logcat for errors: `adb logcat | grep "User action"`
+4. Try simpler code: `console.log('test');`
+
